      • updateUserOnKill

        public int updateUserOnKill(OnKillUpdateWrapper wrapper)
                     throws InvalidTokenException,
                            InvalidSessionException,
                            InvalidUserException,
                            InvalidListException,
                            InvalidLocationException
        Updates the Users involved in an assassination (When a User attempts to eliminate its target)
        Parameters:
        wrapper - See OnKillUpdateWrapper
        Returns:
        1 if the assassination resulted in a win, or 0 if there was no win, but the target was eliminated
        Throws:
        InvalidTokenException - Throws if Token did not have an existing or matching authenticator or was expired
        InvalidSessionException - Throws if the Session trying to use doesn't exist
        InvalidUserException - Throws if the User who is trying to eliminate does not exist
        InvalidListException - Shoudn't happen if the other Exceptions weren't thrown
        InvalidLocationException - Throws if the Location tapped on does not contain the User's target
